            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the garlic is fragrant, add your <strong>orzo </strong>to the pan with the juice of 1/4 of the <strong>lemon wedges</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>creamy stock </strong>to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until cooked through – this is your <strong>creamy orzo</strong></p><p>Tip: Stir the orzo occasionally to stop it from sticking!</p>",
