    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the orzo is cooking, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, drain, then add your <strong>jumbo prawns </strong>and the<strong> spinach</strong> and cook for 4-5 min</p><p>Tear in your <strong>'Nduja</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and the juice of 1/4 of the<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lemon wedges </strong>and cook for 2-3 min further or until the prawns are cooked through and the<strong> </strong>’Nduja has broken down – these are your <strong>'Nduja jumbo prawns</strong></p>",
