    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the orzo is cooked through, season generously with <strong>black pepper</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Add the juice of the <strong>remaining lemon wedges </strong>to a bowl with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and a grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your<strong> lemony dressing</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>baby leaf salad</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper</p>",
